We got to keep it in the right perspective, in the right order.

00:30:16.779 --> 00:30:20.299
Jesus said, I am the vine, ye are the branches.

00:30:20.299 --> 00:30:21.299
Sometimes we can get messed up.

00:30:21.299 --> 00:30:25.279
We can get kind of big headed, right, prideful.

00:30:25.279 --> 00:30:29.919
He says this, he that abideth in me and I in him, the same bringeth forth much fruit

00:30:30.059 --> 00:30:34.259
for without me ye can do nothing.

00:30:34.259 --> 00:30:41.859
I'm thankful this evening for the truth and the connection between what God gives to Moses

00:30:41.859 --> 00:30:49.419
in Exodus chapter 3 and further revelation in Exodus chapter 6 with regard to Jehovah

00:30:49.419 --> 00:30:51.059
I am.

00:30:51.059 --> 00:30:52.059
And then we make the connection.

00:30:52.059 --> 00:30:57.279
And we can look at so many verses in the Old Testament, I mean, again, over 6,500 times

00:30:57.379 --> 00:31:00.619
that the name Jehovah is used in the Old Testament.

00:31:00.619 --> 00:31:05.659
We can look at verses after verses after verses to understand the impact that it had on the

00:31:05.659 --> 00:31:06.939
people of God.

00:31:06.939 --> 00:31:12.859
The prophet Isaiah uses the name regularly throughout the book and you find so many references

00:31:12.859 --> 00:31:19.659
in this evening as we would understand the connection to the Lord Jesus Christ, our Lord

00:31:19.659 --> 00:31:23.539
and Savior and what he did on that cross.

00:31:23.539 --> 00:31:28.719
And then as he rose conquering sin, death, and the grave and the fulfillment that we

00:31:28.719 --> 00:31:34.959
see in Hebrews chapter 9 and 10, the picture from the Old Testament day of atonement, how

00:31:34.959 --> 00:31:38.319
we should rejoice this evening.

00:31:38.319 --> 00:31:51.379
And the reality tonight is that when we understand Jehovah I am to be the self-existent one,

00:31:51.379 --> 00:31:56.679
we don't have to get flustered by the question, who created God?

00:31:56.679 --> 00:31:58.679
It's a silly question.

00:31:58.679 --> 00:32:02.759
It's a silly question.

00:32:02.759 --> 00:32:04.359
God created all things.

00:32:04.359 --> 00:32:05.359
God is.

00:32:05.359 --> 00:32:07.479
He is the self-existent one.

00:32:07.479 --> 00:32:13.119
In fact, I remember having a conversation with someone at some point in the past and

00:32:13.119 --> 00:32:19.239
they were being a little critical about the fact that, you know, we typically just refer

00:32:19.299 --> 00:32:21.899
to God as God or the Lord or something like that.

00:32:21.899 --> 00:32:27.419
We don't use some of his proper names and they were talking about some of the proper

00:32:27.419 --> 00:32:31.839
names and I asked them, well, what does Jehovah mean?

00:32:31.839 --> 00:32:34.579
And they didn't even know.

00:32:34.579 --> 00:32:37.179
They didn't even know what it meant.

00:32:37.179 --> 00:32:41.179
The self-existent one, the one who is.

00:32:41.179 --> 00:32:44.619
He is the present God.

00:32:44.619 --> 00:32:47.299
Think about this just for a moment this evening.

00:32:47.359 --> 00:32:55.319
The one who is the self-existent God, the one who his name means to be, he is in the

00:32:55.319 --> 00:33:01.079
present tense and he is all that you need.

00:33:01.079 --> 00:33:03.399
And that's important for us to understand.

00:33:03.399 --> 00:33:07.719
I preached a message at the end of last year, it was the introductory message for our study

00:33:07.719 --> 00:33:13.899
this year on God's grace is sufficient and I kind of hammered the point on that Sunday

00:33:13.899 --> 00:33:19.279
morning that God's grace is sufficient.

00:33:19.279 --> 00:33:25.599
And I repeatedly, repeatedly in that message focused on that little word is.

00:33:25.599 --> 00:33:30.779
Because in the moment that you need God's grace, God's grace is sufficient.

00:33:30.779 --> 00:33:34.039
It's not that God said my grace was sufficient.

00:33:34.039 --> 00:33:36.979
It's not that God says my grace will be sufficient.

00:33:36.979 --> 00:33:45.219
He is always in the present tense and he says my grace is sufficient.

00:33:45.219 --> 00:33:47.419
He's all I need.

00:33:47.419 --> 00:33:48.419
There's a little chorus.

00:33:48.419 --> 00:33:53.539
It's not in our song book, a little chorus I remember singing years ago, Christ is all

00:33:53.539 --> 00:33:54.539
I need.

00:33:54.539 --> 00:33:55.579
And it's just a little chorus.

00:33:55.579 --> 00:34:00.059
I think there might be like five other words other than Christ is all I need in the whole

00:34:00.059 --> 00:34:01.059
chorus.

00:34:01.059 --> 00:34:06.019
But it's just that reminder that truly he's all I need.

00:34:06.059 --> 00:34:09.779
He is the Lord God Almighty.

00:34:09.779 --> 00:34:13.739
He is Jehovah, the self-existent one.

00:34:13.739 --> 00:34:17.539
And this evening, whatever it is that you need, someone said it this way, when God said

00:34:17.539 --> 00:34:21.939
I am, he said I am whatever you need me to be, I am.

00:34:21.939 --> 00:34:25.419
And I think that's a nice little statement.

00:34:25.419 --> 00:34:29.459
Whatever you need tonight, Jehovah.

00:34:29.459 --> 00:34:34.239
We'll look at a number of the other names, especially those compound names that reveal

00:34:34.239 --> 00:34:41.439
to us God is the Lord, our peace, the Lord who provides, the Lord who heals, the Lord...

00:34:41.439 --> 00:34:48.899
I mean, go on and on and on and what joy in knowing this proper name of God, Jehovah.

00:34:48.899 --> 00:34:49.899
Let's pray together.

00:34:49.899 --> 00:34:52.639
Father, how we love you.

00:34:52.639 --> 00:34:53.879
We thank you for loving us.

00:34:53.879 --> 00:34:59.559
We thank you for your word and we thank you for the truth that you've revealed to us.

00:34:59.679 --> 00:35:07.159
We thank you for the beauty of your word and the fulfillment and how we can go from passage

00:35:07.159 --> 00:35:08.159
to passage.

00:35:08.159 --> 00:35:13.519
You said that no scriptures of any private interpretation, no were to compare scripture

00:35:13.519 --> 00:35:14.519
with scripture.

00:35:14.519 --> 00:35:21.919
And God, we thank you for the truth that you have given to us in the New Testament as a

00:35:21.919 --> 00:35:25.679
fulfillment of that which you had previously revealed in the Old Testament.

00:35:25.679 --> 00:35:28.819
We thank you, God, for redemption.

00:35:28.819 --> 00:35:33.519
Thank you for redeeming the nation of Israel from Egyptian bondage.

00:35:33.519 --> 00:35:39.659
But this evening, more importantly, we thank you for redeeming us from the penalty of sin.

00:35:39.659 --> 00:35:45.779
What a joy to know as we would have the privilege of singing redeemed, how I love to proclaim

00:35:45.779 --> 00:35:48.779
it, redeemed by the blood of the Lamb.

00:35:48.779 --> 00:35:54.379
Lord, I thank you and I praise you and I pray that you'd help us, Lord, to be busy about

00:35:54.379 --> 00:35:59.539
telling others about you, the way, the truth, and the life.

00:35:59.539 --> 00:36:00.539
Bless our time of prayer.

00:36:00.539 --> 00:36:01.539
We pray that you'd be honored and glorified.

00:36:01.539 --> 00:36:04.379
And for it's in Christ's name we pray, amen.

